How long have you
been off your medication?

253
00:28:09,022 --> 00:28:10,398
Are you gonna let me in or no?

254
00:28:10,565 --> 00:28:12,067
Is my audition finished?

255
00:28:12,108 --> 00:28:14,527
You need a dance
or a little song or something?

256
00:28:14,694 --> 00:28:17,822
No, but I do need to see your arm.

257
00:28:19,074 --> 00:28:20,825
Congratulations, guys.

258
00:28:20,909 --> 00:28:24,996
You brought me to the only rehab
that doesn't take drug addicts.

259
00:28:25,080 --> 00:28:26,081
I didn't make the cut, let's go.

260
00:28:26,122 --> 00:28:28,083
- This isn't a detox center, you know that.
- Yeah, but...

261
00:28:28,166 --> 00:28:29,542
You need to bring her
back when she's clean.

262
00:28:29,626 --> 00:28:31,961
- Are you kidding me?
- Like... Is that a joke?

263
00:28:32,045 --> 00:28:33,525
- Guys...
- Guys, just give me a second.

264
00:28:33,546 --> 00:28:35,882
Conrad, let her detox here.
What's the problem?

265
00:28:36,216 --> 00:28:38,760
We're not equipped, we're not insured
to deal with detoxing.

266
00:28:38,843 --> 00:28:41,221
You can't take drug addicts?
Then who gets rehabbed here?

267
00:28:41,262 --> 00:28:42,722
Bring her back in five days.

268
00:28:42,847 --> 00:28:45,183
She can't sit in a room
without drugs for five days.

269
00:28:45,225 --> 00:28:46,559
That's why we came here.
That's why she's here.

270
00:28:46,643 --> 00:28:48,353
Okay, everybody just needs to calm down.

271
00:28:48,395 --> 00:28:50,814
No, you don't understand how hard it was
to get her here.

272
00:28:50,897 --> 00:28:55,068
Stop! Stop! This is why I can't.

273
00:29:00,448 --> 00:29:02,701
Let's just go, please.

274
00:29:12,711 --> 00:29:15,380
My God. Who does that?

275
00:29:15,505 --> 00:29:16,665
So how do you know this girl?

276
00:29:18,299 --> 00:29:19,884
We just met.

277
00:29:21,845 --> 00:29:23,722
Come on, let her in.

278
00:29:24,472 --> 00:29:28,018
Look, you saw her arm.
She could trigger the other girls. I can't...

279
00:29:28,059 --> 00:29:30,437
I can't risk a fresh cut.
You know the deal, David.

280
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:32,272
Just bring her back.

281
00:29:32,397 --> 00:29:33,732
Hey.

282
00:29:34,399 --> 00:29:37,736
Where you been,
why haven't I seen you at meetings lately?

283
00:29:38,361 --> 00:29:40,238
You know, business.

284
00:29:40,321 --> 00:29:42,449
Yeah. I know bullshit.

285
00:29:42,782 --> 00:29:45,660
This might be a very good thing
to happen for you, you know.

286
00:29:46,369 --> 00:29:50,540
- Nothing is happening to me.
- Five days, no drugs, no new cuts.

287
00:29:50,665 --> 00:29:52,042
I can't commit to that!

288
00:29:52,083 --> 00:29:53,877
Well, I remember somebody
committing to that for you.

289
00:29:54,085 --> 00:29:56,671
- You're an asshole.
- Bring her back.

290
00:29:57,047 --> 00:29:58,923
I can't do that.

291
00:30:03,553 --> 00:30:06,848
Wow, I haven't seen your parents
in, like, forever.

292
00:30:06,931 --> 00:30:08,350
Yeah, me neither.

293
00:30:17,942 --> 00:30:19,944
- Renee!
- Hey, baby!

294
00:30:20,070 --> 00:30:23,073
Oh, my God, I haven't seen you in forever.

295
00:30:23,114 --> 00:30:24,157
Think you can stay?

296
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:27,535
April, honey, go inside, please.

297
00:30:27,577 --> 00:30:28,661
Can Renee come in?

298
00:30:29,204 --> 00:30:31,289
Honey, inside, please.

299
00:30:34,250 --> 00:30:37,170
- Hey, Dad.
- Hello, Renee.

300
00:30:37,462 --> 00:30:38,838
I...

301
00:30:39,631 --> 00:30:42,008
I'm gonna go to rehab in a few days.

302
00:30:42,592 --> 00:30:45,136
Good, good, that's really good.

303
00:30:45,929 --> 00:30:47,472
And I just need to...

304
00:30:47,555 --> 00:30:53,728
Actually, I was wondering if I could
stay here for, like, just until I go.

305
00:30:53,895 --> 00:30:55,605
I'm sorry, I can't do that.

306
00:30:55,689 --> 00:30:57,107
Crap.

307
00:30:57,899 --> 00:30:59,067
He's not gonna let her stay.

308
00:30:59,734 --> 00:31:01,236
Can she stay at your place?

309
00:31:01,277 --> 00:31:04,948
No. My dad's not into sleepovers.
Not since my mom died.

310
00:31:05,031 --> 00:31:06,408
She can stay with me.

311
00:31:06,616 --> 00:31:08,118
Yeah, that's a great idea, Dylan.

312
00:31:08,201 --> 00:31:09,619
What's wrong with his?

313
00:31:09,703 --> 00:31:12,455
I don't know.
Just his mother being a raging alcoholic

314
00:31:12,539 --> 00:31:14,791
might get in the way. No big deal.

315
00:31:14,874 --> 00:31:17,085
Dad, I literally don't have anywhere else
I can go.

316
00:31:17,210 --> 00:31:20,797
I'm sorry. I promised myself
it wasn't going to happen again, okay?

317
00:31:21,715 --> 00:31:23,842
And the last time you stayed here,

318
00:31:23,883 --> 00:31:26,553
- it was your... Please just listen to me.
- I know... No, don't...

319
00:31:26,594 --> 00:31:28,388
It was your sister who found your blood.

320
00:31:28,430 --> 00:31:31,725
Okay, I am aware of that.
It's not going to happen ever again.

321
00:31:31,766 --> 00:31:34,227
You don't understand, Dad.
If you don't let me stay here...

322
00:31:34,352 --> 00:31:35,729
- No, I do understand.
- ...I have nowhere else to go.

323
00:31:36,021 --> 00:31:38,440
Five minutes.
Thank you, thank you very much.

324
00:31:38,565 --> 00:31:39,566
- David?
- Yes?

325
00:31:39,607 --> 00:31:41,609
- Can she stay with you?
- No, she can't.

326
00:31:41,693 --> 00:31:43,153
I can't let it happen to your sister
and I can't...

327
00:31:43,236 --> 00:31:45,905
Dad, you can't!
You have to let me stay here.

328
00:31:46,114 --> 00:31:48,408
- Please.
- No. She's your friend, mate.

329
00:31:48,450 --> 00:31:49,743
But you just stood up in church and said

330
00:31:49,784 --> 00:31:51,453
how important it is for people
to have strong support.

331
00:31:51,536 --> 00:31:54,039
I know what I just did and I am having
a tough time at the moment, Dylan.

332
00:31:54,080 --> 00:31:55,749
- I've got a lot on my...
- Please. I know. So is she!

333
00:31:55,915 --> 00:31:57,542
- You love me so much?
- I would do anything for you, but...

334
00:31:57,625 --> 00:31:59,627
You don't want me to sleep in my room
so I can get better?

335
00:31:59,711 --> 00:32:01,171
- Dylan, please.
- ...go home to something like this.

336
00:32:01,212 --> 00:32:02,839
- Can I just have five seconds to try...
- She trusts you.

337
00:32:02,881 --> 00:32:05,550
- And you have a huge house.
- You have a huge house?

338
00:32:05,717 --> 00:32:07,886
- Well, it's big!
- Fine!

339
00:32:09,554 --> 00:32:11,639
You shut up, and you stop sulking,

340
00:32:11,723 --> 00:32:14,184
and you're all staying at my place.

341
00:32:14,351 --> 00:32:15,477
...one of the things I can't do...

342
00:32:15,560 --> 00:32:16,644
You would not do anything

343
00:32:16,728 --> 00:32:18,480
because you're not letting me sleep
where I need to sleep!

344
00:32:18,563 --> 00:32:19,606
Mr. Yohe, my name's David McKenna.

345
00:32:19,689 --> 00:32:22,400
Do you mind if Renee stays with me
for a couple of days?

346
00:32:24,319 --> 00:32:25,759
She's gonna need to get some things.

347
00:32:54,974 --> 00:32:56,393
Lovely.

348
00:33:04,275 --> 00:33:06,736
You moving out or you moving in?

349
00:33:06,778 --> 00:33:07,946
Not sure yet.

350
00:33:08,029 --> 00:33:09,072
This is fancy.

351
00:33:10,907 --> 00:33:12,367
- Hey, Renee.
- Yep.

352
00:33:13,201 --> 00:33:17,414
In this house
there's no booze and no drugs. Okay?

353
00:33:17,497 --> 00:33:20,542
Just sleep, coffee and cigarettes.

354
00:33:20,583 --> 00:33:23,063
My number one rule, we don't get tired
and we don't get hungry.

355
00:33:25,046 --> 00:33:26,047
Okay.

356
00:33:26,131 --> 00:33:27,966
- You in?
- I'm in.

357
00:33:28,216 --> 00:33:29,718
Let's do it.

358
00:33:31,261 --> 00:33:35,223
Okay, kitchen, my quarters, hot tub,
you lot can park it upstairs,

359
00:33:35,306 --> 00:33:37,600
middle room's my office, no kids allowed.
We clear?

360
00:33:37,684 --> 00:33:40,437
And you got first dibs. You two...

361
00:33:47,652 --> 00:33:50,363
Addiction is a very
complicated relationship.

362
00:33:50,572 --> 00:33:52,574
We've been friends with Renee
for, like, 12 years.

363
00:33:52,657 --> 00:33:54,659
- Trust me, we know.
- Okay, all right.

364
00:33:54,743 --> 00:33:56,077
This is not Renee.

365
00:33:57,245 --> 00:34:00,582
<i>You have to think invasion of
the Body Snatchersor something, okay?</i>

366
00:34:01,583 --> 00:34:04,669
Every single thing in her,
every fiber of her being

367
00:34:04,711 --> 00:34:07,005
wants one thing,
is thinking about one thing,

368
00:34:07,047 --> 00:34:09,924
cares about one thing and it's not you,
and it's not me.

369
00:34:10,258 --> 00:34:12,052
It's drugs, okay?

370
00:34:12,344 --> 00:34:13,845
So what do we do?

371
00:34:13,887 --> 00:34:15,138
What we do is...

372
00:34:15,221 --> 00:34:19,267
Okay, the game plan is distractions,
distractions, distractions. Okay?

373
00:34:19,351 --> 00:34:21,895
Dylan, you're on snack duty, okay?

374
00:34:21,936 --> 00:34:24,856
Take Renee, don't let her out of
your sight. Come straight back.

375
00:34:24,939 --> 00:34:27,525
She'll ask you to go someplace else,
you don't go, you don't deviate,

376
00:34:27,567 --> 00:34:29,944
you come back here.
Half an hour, 30 minutes. All right?

377
00:34:30,028 --> 00:34:32,280
Or I'm coming after you. Jessie?

378
00:34:33,031 --> 00:34:35,951
Jessie, take all the knives and anything
sharp in the house and hide them.

379
00:34:36,076 --> 00:34:37,956
You want me to
hide all the knives in the house?

380
00:34:38,036 --> 00:34:39,746
Did you see her arm?

381
00:34:41,331 --> 00:34:44,042
Look, all the ways you want to punish Renee
for being a shit friend

382
00:34:44,209 --> 00:34:46,252
will pale in comparison to the ways
Renee will punish herself.

383
00:34:46,336 --> 00:34:48,254
Now get on with it.

384
00:34:49,047 --> 00:34:50,882
All right, let's go.

385
00:34:51,091 --> 00:34:54,052
Dylan? Don't forget my Lucky Charms.

386
00:34:59,683 --> 00:35:02,727
Animal crackers! Oh, yes!

387
00:35:05,522 --> 00:35:07,065
I missed you.

388
00:35:07,524 --> 00:35:10,360
Yeah, I mean, why did we stop hanging out
in the first place?

389
00:35:10,485 --> 00:35:13,655
What is this? What are we doing?
We're hanging out.

390
00:35:13,738 --> 00:35:15,365
We used to hang out,
like, every day together

391
00:35:15,407 --> 00:35:17,867
and now you're a completely
different person

392
00:35:17,909 --> 00:35:20,078
doing different things and I don't know...

393
00:35:20,161 --> 00:35:22,288
Different things?

394
00:35:23,164 --> 00:35:24,444
You know what I'm talking about.

395
00:35:24,541 --> 00:35:26,381
- I know what you're talking about.
- You know.

396
00:35:26,710 --> 00:35:28,962
Why did you do that to your arm?

397
00:35:31,381 --> 00:35:33,425
It just looked right.

398
00:35:33,508 --> 00:35:37,429
Well, I like the way you look without it.
'Cause it's not true.

399
00:35:37,762 --> 00:35:39,282
Crap, sorry. I didn't know this was...

400
00:35:39,764 --> 00:35:42,308
No, no, no. I got this. I got this.

401
00:35:42,475 --> 00:35:44,060
Okay.

402
00:37:37,799 --> 00:37:39,926
Whoa, McKenna, whoa!

403
00:37:40,010 --> 00:37:41,553
Jamie!

404
00:37:42,554 --> 00:37:44,556
You nearly gave me a heart attack,
you wanker.

405
00:37:44,639 --> 00:37:46,119
When did we start sounding the alarm?

406
00:37:46,725 --> 00:37:47,726
Today.

407
00:37:47,767 --> 00:37:49,047
And when did we get new friends?

408
00:37:49,269 --> 00:37:50,270
Keeping her safe.

409
00:37:51,896 --> 00:37:53,565
- Obvious enough.
- Renee,

410
00:37:53,648 --> 00:37:57,152
meet Jamie, my sometimes housemate,
who I'm guessing missed his flight.

411
00:37:57,402 --> 00:37:58,570
Jessie. Good night.

412
00:37:58,945 --> 00:38:01,072
Dylan took your room,
so you can bunk with him.

413
00:38:01,573 --> 00:38:04,659
All right! Bunk buddies. See you up there.

414
00:38:04,743 --> 00:38:08,079
This is David McKenna.
Everything's fine, false alarm.

415
00:38:12,083 --> 00:38:14,669
Want some Lucky Charms?

416
00:38:19,215 --> 00:38:24,054
I know this isn't any of my business,
but you all right, Renee?

417
00:38:24,137 --> 00:38:26,514
I'm a coozer.

418
00:38:26,765 --> 00:38:30,185
- A coozer?
- It's coke and booze together.

419
00:38:30,226 --> 00:38:32,604
I made it up, do you like it?

420
00:38:34,689 --> 00:38:37,901
Yeah. I don't think McKenna coozes much.

421
00:38:38,234 --> 00:38:39,903
He's such a quitter.

422
00:38:40,945 --> 00:38:43,573
So what's you're... Who do you...
What's your deal?

423
00:38:45,116 --> 00:38:47,619
I'm actually a lot more
interested in you right now.

424
00:38:47,702 --> 00:38:48,745
I'll bet.

425
00:38:51,748 --> 00:38:55,418
I need a place to detox for a few days
till I go to rehab

426
00:38:55,502 --> 00:38:59,589
and McKenna is donating to my charity.

427
00:39:00,632 --> 00:39:02,467
Nosy.

428
00:39:02,717 --> 00:39:05,095
I didn't mean to be nosy.

429
00:39:05,553 --> 00:39:07,639
I'm just really...

430
00:39:08,848 --> 00:39:10,141
That's really brave.

431
00:39:10,725 --> 00:39:12,394
I'm happy for you.

432
00:39:15,105 --> 00:39:16,731
Why doesn't he have knives?

433
00:39:20,568 --> 00:39:21,569
So what do you do?

434
00:39:22,904 --> 00:39:26,908
I am a rep for a surf company.

435
00:39:27,283 --> 00:39:31,246
McKenna's nice enough to let me crash here
when I'm in town.

436
00:39:31,663 --> 00:39:33,581
- You're like a traveling salesman?
- Yeah.

437
00:39:34,082 --> 00:39:35,709
Legit job.

438
00:39:35,792 --> 00:39:38,586
Office. Grown-up stuff.

439
00:39:39,212 --> 00:39:42,007
But what I really wanna do is write.

440
00:39:44,843 --> 00:39:46,761
You like Paper Route?

441
00:39:46,845 --> 00:39:48,847
They're playing at
the Florida Music Fest tomorrow.

442
00:39:49,597 --> 00:39:51,878
Yeah. We should go.
You think the warden will let you out?

443
00:39:51,891 --> 00:39:54,060
I will dig my way out.

444
00:39:54,894 --> 00:39:56,479
Right on.

445
00:39:57,939 --> 00:39:59,983
So you out tomorrow morning or...

446
00:40:00,358 --> 00:40:02,569
Actually the day after,
if that's okay with you.

447
00:40:02,652 --> 00:40:04,237
Yeah, the more the merrier.

448
00:40:04,404 --> 00:40:07,032
All right, thank you.

449
00:40:07,157 --> 00:40:08,950
No problem.

450
00:40:10,452 --> 00:40:12,328
Appreciate it.

451
00:40:13,705 --> 00:40:16,708
And congratulations on
your new life, Renee.

452
00:40:18,043 --> 00:40:20,211
- Good night.
- Bye!

453
00:40:24,549 --> 00:40:26,760
Pretty good.

454
00:40:28,345 --> 00:40:29,596
How are you feeling?

455
00:40:30,055 --> 00:40:31,848
Like my soul got kicked in the nuts.

456
00:40:33,266 --> 00:40:34,476
Good.

457
00:40:34,684 --> 00:40:39,064
Well, not good that you feel
like your soul's been kicked in the balls,

458
00:40:39,439 --> 00:40:42,776
but it's good you're being honest.
Secrets make you sick.

459
00:40:43,735 --> 00:40:45,070
I like that, McKenna.

460
00:40:45,195 --> 00:40:47,364
- Remember it.
- Yes, sir.

461
00:40:51,076 --> 00:40:52,660
Thank you

462
00:40:53,745 --> 00:40:55,372
for all of this.

463
00:40:56,748 --> 00:40:58,868
Somebody did it for me,
you'll do it for someone else.

464
00:41:00,085 --> 00:41:02,545
All right, thanks for the sandwich.

465
00:41:03,213 --> 00:41:04,798
Sleep tight.

466
00:41:21,314 --> 00:41:22,774
This is slave labor.

467
00:41:22,982 --> 00:41:24,943
I prefer the term internship.

468
00:41:25,068 --> 00:41:26,778
It's all gonna be back next week.

469
00:41:27,153 --> 00:41:29,406
So will you. It's a test of wills, mate.

470
00:41:30,407 --> 00:41:32,117
- Hey.
- There she is!

471
00:41:32,367 --> 00:41:34,369
You all right, sleeping beauty?

472
00:41:38,248 --> 00:41:41,334
You have an extra one of those...
Thank you.

473
00:41:42,627 --> 00:41:44,129
Hey, boss?

474
00:41:44,295 --> 00:41:47,215
I have three...
No, I have four questions for you.

475
00:41:47,382 --> 00:41:50,218
- I'll answer two. Maybe.
- Okay.

476
00:41:50,343 --> 00:41:52,095
One, why don't you have any furniture?

477
00:41:52,178 --> 00:41:53,722
Two, where'd you get your tattoo,

478
00:41:53,847 --> 00:41:58,601
three, how come you left England,
and four, I'll ask you later.

479
00:41:58,727 --> 00:42:00,395
One, I just haven't found
the right sofa yet,

480
00:42:00,437 --> 00:42:03,606
I wish people would stop pressuring me,
and two, I got that bad boy in prison.

481
00:42:03,732 --> 00:42:05,275
Prison? What did you do?

482
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:07,736
Only answering two questions.

483
00:42:08,069 --> 00:42:11,072
- Hey! Right on.
- Hey, Jamie!

484
00:42:11,156 --> 00:42:12,240
Looking great, guys.

485
00:42:12,532 --> 00:42:14,993
So what are you doing
your last night in Orlando?

486
00:42:15,076 --> 00:42:17,495
I was thinking Florida Music Fest.

487
00:42:18,538 --> 00:42:20,819
I mean, your band's playing, right?
We'll all go together.

488
00:42:21,041 --> 00:42:24,210
You have bands? McKenna, I wanna go.

489
00:42:24,502 --> 00:42:27,222
One band, and, no, you can't go,
you're staying with the babysitters.

490
00:42:27,964 --> 00:42:29,424
I thought she needed distractions.

491
00:42:29,507 --> 00:42:32,510
Yeah, if there's music,
I'm not thinking about drugs.

492
00:42:32,635 --> 00:42:35,638
No, there's no drugs at a music festival.
It's a great idea.

493
00:42:36,014 --> 00:42:38,558
Exactly. I don't have extra tickets anyway,
so it's settled.

494
00:42:38,725 --> 00:42:39,851
Turns out Hurley's sponsoring the event.

495
00:42:39,893 --> 00:42:43,521
Made a call, got us VIP treatment
